Dune is a reputable global retailer offering a diverse selection of products includng accessories, clothings and phones. With a growing presence in 14 countries and a tram of over 70,000 d employees, teh company pride itself on providing affordable options for everyone. from fashion-forward trendsetters to multi-generational families, Dunes strives to offer great quality essentials and stoand out style that cater to a wide range of customers.

As the newly appointed Data Scientist, my first task is to analys the company's sales data from the previous year and provide acrionable insights and recommendations. This analysis will help identify areas of opportunities and inform future business decisions aimed at improving performance and increasing profitability

Exploratoty data analysis (EDA) is the process of analysing and summarising data to gain insights and understand the underlying patterns and relatioships. The main objectives of EDA is to identify and explore the primary characteristics of patterns of the data and anomalies or outliers that may impact subsequent analysis. It invoves

  • Data cleaning
  • Data visualisation
  • statistical analysis

Dealing with missing data¶

  • MCAR (missing completely at random) values randomly missing not dependent on other values
  • MAR (missinng at random) dependent on some other additional features
  • MNAR (missing not at random) there is a reason why these values are missing

There are several methods of imputing missing data incluing the measures of central tendecies, regression imputation, and multiple imputation. Measure of central tendency involves replacing missing values with either Mean, Median, and Mode of the values. Regression imputation involves using other variables in the data set to predict missing values

  • Mode can replace missing values for categorical data
  • Mean or Median for numerical depending on if you have outliers or not
  • Regression method is to predict the missing data. It is more advanced

## Let us group customer age group by cretaing a function

def age_group(x):
    if x <= 25:
        return "<= 25 Youth"
    elif x <= 40:
        return "26 - 40 Young Adult"
    elif x <= 60:
        return "46 - 60 Older Adult"
    else:
        return ">60 Elders"
    
## Apply function to data using the statement [.apply(age_group)]
#create another colunm for age 


df['age_group'] = df['Customer_Age'].apply(age_group)

## Let us calculate Profit and Loss
#Quantity, Revenue and Profit

# create a new column for cost
# total cost(cost) = quantity * unit cost
# revenue = quantity * unit price 
# profit = revenue - cost


df['cost'] = df['Quantity'] * df['Unit_Cost']
df['revenue'] = df['Quantity'] * df['Unit_Price']
df['profit'] = df['revenue'] - df['cost']

# customer category and profit

fig, axs = plt.subplots(nrows= 2, ncols=3, figsize=(25,10)) # to create 6 plots
